{"parse":{"title":"Anarchy in Action","pageid":231775,"revid":833953305,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Anarchy in Action <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anarchy+in+Action&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BColin+Ward%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1973&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BAllen+%26+Unwin%7CGeorge+Allen+%26+Unwin%5D%5D+and+%5B%5BFreedom+Press%5D%5D+%28UK%29%2C+%5B%5BHarper+%26+Row%5D%5D+%28US%29&amp;rft.pages=157+pp+%27%27%28first+edition%29%27%27\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Anarchy_in_Action_-_Colin_Ward_-_1973.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Anarchy in Action - Colin Ward - 1973.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9e/Anarchy_in_Action_-_Colin_Ward_-_1973.jpg/220px-Anarchy_in_Action_-_Colin_Ward_-_1973.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"337\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9e/Anarchy_in_Action_-_Colin_Ward_-_1973.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"255\" data-file-height=\"391\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Colin_Ward\" title=\"Colin Ward\">Colin Ward</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited Kingdom</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Anarchism\" title=\"Anarchism\">Anarchism</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Allen_%26_Unwin\" title=\"Allen &amp; Unwin\">George Allen &amp; Unwin</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Freedom_Press\" title=\"Freedom Press\">Freedom Press</a> (UK), <a href=\"/wiki/Harper_%26_Row\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Harper &amp; Row\">Harper &amp; Row</a> (US)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n1973</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n157 pp <i>(first edition)</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0043210163\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0043210163\">0043210163</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Dewey_Decimal_Classification\" title=\"Dewey Decimal Classification\">Dewey Decimal</a></div></th><td>\n335.83</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Anarchy in Action</b></i> is a book exploring <a href=\"/wiki/Anarchism\" title=\"Anarchism\">anarchist</a> thought and practice, written by <a href=\"/wiki/Colin_Ward\" title=\"Colin Ward\">Colin Ward</a> and first published in 1973.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book is a seminal introduction to anarchism but differs considerably to others by concentrating on the possibility of an anarchism rooted in everyday experience, and not necessarily linked to industrial and political struggles. His ideas are heavily influenced by <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Kropotkin\" title=\"Peter Kropotkin\">Peter Kropotkin</a> and his concept of <a href=\"/wiki/Mutual_aid_(organization_theory)\" title=\"Mutual aid (organization theory)\">Mutual Aid</a>. Ward bases his text on evidence from <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology\" title=\"Sociology\">sociology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Anthropology\" title=\"Anthropology\">anthropology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Cybernetics\" title=\"Cybernetics\">cybernetics</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Industrial_psychology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Industrial psychology\">industrial psychology</a>, and from the experience of housing, <a href=\"/wiki/Town_planning\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Town planning\">town planning</a>, education, work, play and <a href=\"/wiki/Social_welfare\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Social welfare\">social welfare</a>. Ward argues for anarchist alternatives to the universal governmental and <a href=\"/wiki/Hierarchical\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hierarchical\">hierarchical</a> systems of <a href=\"/wiki/Social_organisation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Social organisation\">social organisation</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> This bucks a number of conventional trends of the socialist left, because he is quite critical of the welfare state.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotations\">Quotations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Anarchy_in_Action&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Quotations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>\"The argument of this book is that an anarchist society, a society which organizes itself without authority, is always in existence, like a seed beneath the snow, buried under the weight of the state and its bureaucracy, capitalism and its waste, privilege and its injustices, nationalism and its suicidal loyalties, religious differences and their superstitious separatism.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Anarchy_in_Action&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/society/2010/feb/22/colin-ward-obituary\">\"Colin Ward obituary\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i>. 22 February 2010<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">20 August</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Colin+Ward+obituary&amp;rft.date=2010-02-22&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsociety%2F2010%2Ffeb%2F22%2Fcolin-ward-obituary&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnarchy+in+Action\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books/about/Anarchy_in_Action.html?id=4yl6AAAACAAJ&amp;redir_esc=y\"><i>Anarchy in Action - Colin Ward</i></a>. Google Books<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">20 August</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anarchy+in+Action+-+Colin+Ward&amp;rft.pub=Google+Books&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fabout%2FAnarchy_in_Action.html%3Fid%3D4yl6AAAACAAJ%26redir_esc%3Dy&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnarchy+in+Action\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Colin_Ward\" title=\"Colin Ward\">Colin Ward</a> (1973). \"Preface\". <i>Anarchy in Action</i>. George Allen &amp; 